NAME
       clear - clear the terminal screen

SYNOPSIS
       clear [-x] [-T type]
       clear -V

DESCRIPTION
       clear clears the terminal screen and scrollback buffer using ANSI escape
       sequences.  If the -x option is given, only the visible screen is
       cleared and the scrollback buffer is preserved.

OPTIONS
       -x     Do not clear the scrollback buffer (clear visible screen only).

       -T type
              Specify terminal type (accepted for compatibility but ignored;
              the console is always ANSI-compatible).

       -V     Output version information and exit.

DETAILS
       By default, clear sends ESC[H ESC[2J ESC[3J to reset the cursor to the
       top-left corner and clear both the visible screen and the scrollback
       buffer.

       With -x, only ESC[H ESC[2J is sent, preserving the scrollback history.

